101.ezboard.com/umorgenayanamii.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morgen Ayanamii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lorekeeper</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#660000>(2/14/02 11:36:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sisters...a moment of your time.</span><hr size=1> I think this sounds like a great idea Briarboots. <br><br>This is the 2nd or 3rd thing to come up in the past couple of days that is inspiring me to do something similar.  I am already in the middle of rearranging some things so I have more time to spend with my favorite people, i.e., my Sisters and my Brothers.  <br><br>I made 37th level last night, and my options on hunting with my own folk have only gotten more and more limited.  Taking time off or waiting around until folk catch up have gotten old, and I've been losing contact.  I'm a young &quot;player&quot; and I'm still learning what is appropriate to offer for help and what isn't.<br><br>I'm not talking about PLing people exactly, not that I'd know *how*, but it can't *hurt* to have an enchantress hanging out near you, or looking over your shoulder, whether it's for hunting or questing.<br><br>In the last 48 hours, Sneaux and Aliantha and Soyin have talked about grouping with me.  I'd love to.<br><br>So Briarboots, if I may be allowed to use you as an example for my own behavior, I'd like to.  And perhaps you might let me tag along at some point as well.....<br><br>OH.   I'm stuck in a cave in Hollowshade at the moment, with a bunch of hungry Sonic Wolves that keep wandering around.  After I complete my current objective there, I'm going to take Soyin on a tour of Oggok.  Anyone else who wants to come hang out in Oggok is welcome.  After that I'm probably going back to this cursed cave, lol, to help Aliantha here.  We'll need 2 or 3 more 30+ish folk to handle that.<br><br>I'm probably looking at one afternoon/evening a week, probably during the week, where I'm just going to make myself available to my Sibs..  In addition to that, I'm going to start checking if anyone needs me in the guildchat first, *before* I talk to anyone else, when I have a free block of time coming up.<br><br>Morgen Ayanamii, Circle of Sisters <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ubriarboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Briarboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/02 12:11:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sisters...a moment of your time.</span><hr size=1> Morgen,<br><br>Sorry to hear you are feeling my pain.  You are welcome to come stand around with me and chaparone the youngers when ever you want. <br><br>When you head back to the sonic wolves do check with me.  If I am available I'd be glad to try and assist.<br><br>ooc:  <br>You bring up an interesting point there. Power leveling.  I sure hope what I'm doing isn't concidered wrong.  If indeed it is then I've been wrong the entire time I've played this character.  I've always been rather liberal with the buffs and heals when passing through the newbie hunting areas.  Now, hanging out there to make sure friends don't get in over thier heads or survive when they do.  I'd like to think that's not power leveling, but then if it is I've been power leveling strangers forever.  If that is bad, should I then stop finding brothers who are hunting and hang out with them outside thier group throwing buffs and heals on thier group when needed?  That's really all I have to do when I cannot find a group to hunt what I want to hunt.  Well, I suppose I could wander around the karanas foraging plains pebbles or misty thicket foraging acorns, but well I got sick of that a week ago.<br><br>Since i couldn't figure out a way to say this IC, as soon as we all get into grouping range of you we would be glad to keep you in the loop to fill in for absent members on the scheduled hunt nights.  Who knows.  If this catches on maybe we could startup a second group by that time and do little mini raids on the hunt nights.<br>/ooc<br> <p><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=118018">Briarboots</A> Druid of Karana <BR> Elder of the Clan of Brothers <BR>Master of Initiates<BR>Lord of the Drink</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ubrimose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brimose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/02 6:17:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sisters...a moment of your time.</span><hr size=1> ((all ooc))<br>in my mind, powerleveling is when the younger player specifically asks for the type of help you provide.  Even that is a bit ambiguous, since sometimes requesting help to do a quest (like my ranger ivy armor for example) can be considered by some to be powerleveling.  If the higher player offers it, then there can be reason to provide an IC explanation of it.  Lets face it:  It's not as much fun to roleplay if you're stuck at level 15 forever, you'll wanna get out and get higher levels and better gear.  Assuming that the 'powerleveling' is not abused, I personally see no wrong with your proposal, especially since you are getting bored by yourself anyway.<br><br>'course, it's also 5 am as I write this.  Please let me know if it makes sense or not...<br> <p>Brion (Raydon) <BR>15 Ranger of the Glade, Elder, Treasurer, and Charter Member of the Clan of Brothers on Fironia Vie <BR>Brimose Greymyst <BR>25 Ranger of the Glade, Nameless of Mercy on The Nameless, semi-retired <BR>Leaving my mark all over Norrath... in corpses <BR>Ack!  Ranger Down!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uminuetthetalechaser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minuet the Talechaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#660000>(2/15/02 5:12:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sisters...a moment of your time.</span><hr size=1> &lt;ooc&gt;<br>I don't think we have anything to worry about in regards to powerleveling and Roleplay. As long as we are roleplaying, what is the worry of having a higher level companion accompany us. Of course, I am in no hurry to get to higher levels, theres a lot to do in the 20's and things to get before they TLC out.<br><br>Now, making up all the lost experience from dying, thats a different story. <p>Minuet the Talechaser<br>The enchanting half-elf bard of Qeynos. <br>Circle of Sisters</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ubriarboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Briarboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#660000>(2/16/02 2:06:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sisters...a moment of your time.</span><hr size=1> Minuet,<br><br>Indeed you are correct there.  I didn't realise until I started researching what quests and adventures would appeal to a rogue that not every class get's stiffed on niffty things to quest for until they are in thier 40's.<br><br>I'll be quite content to assist my group mates with aquireing the niffty stuff that is out there for folks in the 20's that actually have quests they can accomplish.  BTW, if anyone know any mid-level druid quests I haven't been able to come across give me a shout.<br><br> <p><A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=118018">Briarboots</A> Druid of Karana <BR> Elder of the Clan of Brothers <BR>Master of Initiates<BR>Lord of the Drink</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/usistermelli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sister Melli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#660000>(2/18/02 3:03:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   !</span><hr size=1> Brairboots! i still have 22 crystalline silks for ye!  Come get them little one! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ubriarboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Briarboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#660000>(2/19/02 7:10:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=271.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: !</span><hr size=1> *Bounce Bounce Bounce*<br><br>guess who wisely left himself bound in Thurgadin??